{#
  Shared bottom of the floating workspace-switcher menu: just the "New
  workspace" CTA. Rendered inside Chrome.jinja (browser-mode inline menu)
  and Sidebar.jinja (the switcher page loaded into the shared modal
  WebContentsView in Electron) so the markup and classes live in one place
  (the icon is the shared Icon16 ``plus`` glyph). The button id
  (#sidebar-new-workspace) is wired up in chrome.js and sidebar.js
  respectively.

  This element is a direct flex child of #sidebar-menu (JinjaX inlines the
  component), so the panel's ``gap-0.5`` (2px) supplies the spacing above it.
#}
<button id="sidebar-new-workspace"
        type="button"
        class="sidebar-action group flex items-center gap-2 h-8 px-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer type-body text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-fill-hover bg-transparent border-0 text-left">
  <Icon16 name="plus" extra="shrink-0" />
  <span>New workspace</span>
</button>
